,Recommended,263820,10139490,"Posted: 16 May, 2014",all,IsmackayoufacE,"Story driven, Crystalis influenced(menus, combat), action-rpg. Very enjoyable. That's pretty much all there is to it but I'll leave some notes for those on the fence with this one...1. Is this a quality game? Yes.2. Is it lengthy? For this type of game, yeah.3. Does the game/development seem amateurish? Not at all.4. Is this Crystalis 2? No. It shares some menus, graphics, and gameplay features, but this has it's own thing going on. With that said, if you were ever wanting a Crystalis sequel, well, this filled that need for me.5. Why is it only $2? I don't know, but don't let that throw you off. It's not cheap because it's bad, ""too indy"", or plain not good enough to charge a higher price. Don't question it. We got lucky.If this is your type of game, I highly recommend EvilQuest. The price makes this one an easy choice."
