,Recommended,263820,29773722,Posted: 7 February,all,Doc Yendor,"I never played Crystalis on the original NES, but after playing through this title, I wish I had.  This game is your classic retro RPG that harkens back to the NES or Super NES era.  This game won't blow you away with a deep story, insightful dialogue, or an inventive combat system, but if you want something simple to get into and is easy to play, you could spend your money on much worse games.You play the role of the bad guy for once on a quest to ultimately destroy the world.  The game can be beaten in under 10 hours if you aim to race through, and offers enough content for that time for a worthwhile experience IF you are into this genre (I am).  If you dig the 8 and 16 bit RPG titles of old, this is recommended.Best of all, this game is GREAT value for the money ($1.99).  I am eager to see what the developers come up with next."
