,Not Recommended,263820,20200561,"Posted: 1 January, 2016",all,Gnur,"This game is a little entertaining, and short. But not good. Without going out of my way to look up the creators' bios, I'm going to say that this is an early effort from a couple of guys who wanted to create a whole game by themselves--design, programming, art, and music--but who weren't experts at any of the above. This is the kind of game you'd expect to find as a curiosity in the ""early portfolio"" section of someone's website while they keep working to develop more mature work. I'm kind of surprised it's up for sale.The art is dull. You'll see every enemy type in the first couple of dungeons, and then it's palette swaps for the rest of the game. Environments, level designs, all forgettable. Bosses are a little bit interesting to look at, but not much.The music is poorly produced and forgettable.The writing is simply miserable. There is no reason to care about the plot or any of the characters. There are no funny or clever lines.The gameplay is tolerable. Controls are generally responsive. But there's nothing to keep you interested. Enemies either rush you or rush you and shoot at you. You respond by whacking them with a sword or axe that doesn't feel all that satisfying to swing, and occasionally with long-cooldown spells. You get periodic armor upgrades that are strictly numbers-up, no gameplay changes or new character art, and a handful of weapons that all do the same thing. I never got frustrated playing, but I never got excited either.I suggest passing on this one."
