,Recommended,263820,17446843,"Posted: 8 August, 2015",all,awkohawnoh,"I'm not usually into 8 bit styled games or anything of the like but Evil Quest certainly overides that. The gameplay is absolutely spot on with great combat, story, characters and general gameplay.Combat: While it is a simple swing your sword (or axe) type of game, it requires just enough timing that it isn't on the end of SUPER HARD OMG I CANT HIT ANYTHING or everything just keeps dying there's no challenge! With different enemies ranging from projectile shooting ones to just regular (easier) ones that only do damage when you touch them, it makes you learn the enemies. There's also magic with many different spells throughout and a charged projectile attack so make things easier on those annoying bosses.Story: It's a fairly straightforward story but provides an interesting direction to the game. Many of the conversations that Galvis has with other characters provides for interesting content and quite a bit of humor.Characters: Aside from Galvis, the other people in towns provide information on direction in the storyline, just enough info that you'll have to pay attention but nothing overly detailed that's confusing so you can get right to the next part.Gameplay: From herbs and potions to spells and weapons, there are quite a few items that can be bought and gathered to increase your stats (attack, defense, all that). The leveling up system in this is also spot on. There's never a time where things are too easy or too hard due to the perfect balance. Certainly bosses can be difficult (as are any enemies you don't understand yet) but once you get the pattern, it's just the right challenge for your level.Overall, great great game, easy to get into and well worth the price."
