76561197982970895,Recommended,263820,14592786,"Posted: 22 February, 2015",all,Lord Pox,"I really liked EvilQuest.This game isn't a timeless classic, and it won't win any prestigious awards. It IS, however, a fun action RPG that offers a decent challenge with a surprising amount of flexibility in play style. It's everything you would expect from an intentionally retro-style game. The graphics and music bring up those good old nostalgic feelings, but EvilQuest stands apart from similar games because of its dedication to its story. While most gamers may be tempted to overlook the story for its simplicity, I found it to be wholly satisfying.Without spoiling too much, I'll say that EvilQuest's story trashes the Good VS Evil in favor of an Evil VS All approach, and it works really well. I found myself caring about what happens next and who the protagonist would encounter. Think about that. These days, it takes a dash of something special in a game to make you actually care about what happens to the people in it, and EvilQuest has that spice.If you want a quick game with a moderate challenge and a rewarding story, you'd do well to grab EvilQuest. Don't sleep on this one."
