,Recommended,263820,16011895,"Posted: 26 May, 2015",all,dj_moyer,"The Good:If you like Final Fantasy 2 or Legend of Zenda and want to be a villain, you'll like this.You get to play as an evil warlord for a change.Levelup mechanic is pretty simple.Combat is REAL TIME.Equipment upgrades and treasure items are not difficult to find.Some exploration is required to find the next area.SOME NPC give useful dialogue to direct you to your destination.Combat is easy:  either swing your weapon or toss magic to kill monsters before they kill you.  Two buttons.Story is funny and engaging.The Bad:Cut-scenes and dialogue faces are crudely drawn (like by hand using Mario Paint).Graphics are reminiscent of NES/SNES rather than super-powered like the current generation of games.Story is a little fun but nothing to really write home about.You don't get a team of friends so if you die it is ALL YOUR FAULT.Most NPC dialogue is useless.Even useful ones who tell you where to go next are a bit vague.Some exploration of the world is required to figure out where you're going.  (Only bad if you're in a hurry.)Music is not so great.After 2/3 of the game (maybe less) the combat and treasure hunting style gets a bit old.Boss fights are not very challenging.  Just use bigger magic and have more HP than regular monsters.The story is linear.  But maybe (if you like FFII or Legend of Zelda) you like that.The Ugly:Every face drawn for dialogue or cut-scenes!  Ha!Full Review:It is very much like an old NES or maybe SNES game in terms of the style.  So it's a bit like FFII or the first Legend of Zelda game but you play the enemy boss trying to conquer the world instead of a team of heroes trying to save it.  You advance the story when you reach a certain place at a certain point and you get a little ""cut scene"" or else a dialogue scene... be warned though the art for these is pretty bad.  Looks like it was hand-drawn by a six-year-old.  Between these scenes you are basically free to roam the world.  You can go from town to town by walking across a desert or a forest or whatever.  You will encounter enemies on the map.  They usually will chase you as soon as they see you.  You may have to fight multiple monsters at once.  Fighting is REAL TIME and simple:  hit them with a weapon or magic to kill them before they get close enough to hit you.  Much like in Zelda.  Enemy attacks vary.  Rats and wolves attack by just running into you (I suppose they get in close and bite you).  Soldiers often swipe at you with swords or lances.  Beware in the first dungeon, those lances have a long reach.  The flaming skulls toss fireballs at you.  Some other monsters can throw lightning bolts that go straight up/down at you and then turn to go straight left/right.  Bosses are like normal monsters but they have different movement and attack patterns and usually a lot more health.  And then you kill enough monsters to levelup.  You get a few free upgraded stats, and you get a few points to allocate as you choose.  The higher your level gets, the more upgrade points you get.  You start with 2 per level, then you get 3 after a while, etc.  Once you make it to town you can also buy upgraded armor, shields, rings, magic spells, and recovery herbs.  And you also find some of that stuff in treasure chests.  Much like Final Fantasy.  So yeah it's a little bit crude but it's DIFFERENT.  If you like the SNES/NES era rpg's (FF1, FF2, Legend of Zelda, etc.) and you feel like playing as the villain, then you'll get a kick out of this.  Not the best game of all time, but it is fun."
