,Recommended,263820,35276957,Posted: 28 September,all,Razonix,"Well, that was a rather unusual experience. You usually play with the good guy and your objective is to save the world, right? In this game, it's the complete opposite: Your goal is to take over the world, and then put an end to it. No, you don't really get a chance to choose if you're going to play the good Samaritan role or not. The mechanics of the game are rather simple, in a certain sense it does bring some resemblance to old school games. The graphics are fairly simple, there's not much else to say about them. The soundtrack isn't quite captivating, but manages to keep you entertained while you're playing. The sound effects are basic, but they don't really affect anything whatsoever. As for the gameplay, there's an interesting combination of melee and different spells, which makes everything more versatile. The story, besides what was already written in the beginning, is pretty shallow and, unfortunately, the game doesn't get to explore the personality of the characters. You simply don't really get to feel anything for anyone (anger, empathy, pity etc.). Overall, if the objective of the game, besides providing some fun, was to make you feel as a sociopath and / or psychopath, then it was a job well done."
